This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with understanding and modelling resources of Internet end hosts. It could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses resource allocation for Internet-distributed applications. The paper also involves statistical analysis and modelling, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with resource management in operating systems, which could place it in the Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the utility of the models in practical applications, which could place it in the Performance (cs.PF) sub-category.
